### Color in UX design  

Colors can convey emotions, signal actions, and add variety.   

Red, attracts a lot of attention. That's why things like exit signs, emergency buttons, and stop signs are red.   
Blue, communicate serenity and feelings of calmness or peace. That's one reason why blue is considered widely appealing.   

color choices and combinations are used in UX design to add emphasis and communicate branding and can impact accessibility.   

Add emphasis  
a focal ponit, an important action you want users to take    
60-30-10 rule, One neutral color makes up 60 percent of the color palette in your design. backgrounds, lines, text    
A second complementary color makes up 30 percent of the palette.   
A third accent color makes up 10 percent of the palette to add emphasis.   


communicate branding, which is the visual appearance and voice of a company.  
color helps define a product's visual identity, making it stand out among competitors.  
these colors are consistent across all products, which makes designs from the brand easy to identify instantly.   


impact the accessibility of designs.  
follow Web Content Accessibility Guidelines, or WCAG, on color contrast standards to make sure your designs are accessible.   

