### Use containment in layouts  

Containment uses visual barriers to keep designs neat and organized.   
Barriers like lines or colors help limit content to a specific section of a design.   

There are four methods of containment: dividers, borders, fill, and shadow.   
dividers, lines that separate sections. They can be simple yet effective tools for quickly breaking up content that doesn't belong together.   
borders, use lines to break up sections of a page. Borders are continuous lines that often form shapes like squares or rectangles.   
fill, assigns colors to borders and shapes, just as you might think the color fills in the object. This makes content stand out, which creates a new focal point within the mockup.   
shadows, create dimension. Often, designers use shadows in combination with borders or fill. Shadows help break up elements even further. You feel like it's coming off the page.     

